- "top 5 customers" refers to the customers with the highest total order values;
- "total order value" is the sum of the product of quantity and final price for all items in all orders for each customer;
- "total amount" is the total amount of the order as recorded in the orders table.

- 'embarked on their journey' refers to the order status 'Shipped';
- 'merely observed' refers to the order action 'View';
- 'belong to a known category' indicates the customer segment is not null.

- 'Waves of order values' refers to the total value of individual orders;
- 'Rise above the tide of the average' means the total value of the order is greater than the average order value;
- 'Shining like beacons of exceptional spending' highlights that these orders stand out due to their higher value.

- 'top spender customers' refers to customers who have the highest total amount spent among their orders;
- 'shipped orders' are orders that have a status of 'Shipped';
- 'total spend' is the sum of the total amounts of all orders for a customer.

- "Total sales" refers to the sum of the product of the quantity and final price of each order item for a product;
- "Average order value" is the mean total amount of orders within a category;
- "Total orders" is the count of orders placed by a customer;
- "More frequently than the average" means the customer has placed more orders than the average number of orders for a specific product.

- 'Titans of revenue' refers to suppliers who generate the highest total revenue from shipped products;
- 'Substantial value' refers to suppliers with the highest average product price;
- 'Actively circulating in the market' refers to products with a status of 'Active';
- 'Successfully delivered to customers' refers to order items with a status of 'Shipped'.

- 'VIP' refers to Very Important Person, a high-value customer segment;
- 'Stand out as the stars' means having the highest revenue;
- 'Performance' refers to the total revenue generated.

- Customer segments are predefined groups of customers based on certain criteria such as purchase behavior, demographics, etc.;
- The average order value is the mean total amount spent by customers in a segment;
- The cumulative total order value is the running total of the total order values within each customer segment.

- "most valuable" refers to the customer with the highest total sales;
- "most loyal" refers to the customer with the highest number of orders;
- "recent orders" are orders placed within the last year.

- 'blossoms' refers to customers;
- 'seeds' refers to orders;
- 'sprout and grow' refers to orders with an active status;
- 'current state' refers to the order status name;
- 'during the year of 2022' refers to the date range from '2022-01-01' to '2022-12-31';
- 'active' refers to both the order status and customer status being active.

- "ships (orders)" refers to the orders in the database;
- "cargo (total amount)" refers to the total amount of the order;
- "captains (customers)" refers to the customers who placed the orders;
- "state (status)" refers to the current status of the order.

- 'most favored product' refers to the product with the highest quantity in each order;
- 'shining star in a constellation' is a metaphor for the top-ranked product;
- 'Tier 1' segment indicates a specific group of high-value or premium customers.
